1
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:20,470
Finding the best short drama director in Korea.

2
00:00:20,470 --> 00:00:23,700
We're left with the last stage before the final.

3
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:28,040
In Round 3, only one of the two survives.

4
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:30,540
It's a 1:1 death match.

5
00:00:30,540 --> 00:00:36,100
Round 3 will also be judged with stop
votes that put everyone in fear.

6
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:37,980
Each viewer's vote counts as one point.

7
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:40,370
But each of Five Stars' votes
will count as 10 points.

8
00:00:40,370 --> 00:00:42,380
The maximum stop count is 100.

9
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:44,700
If all Five Stars press the stop button,

10
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,130
it will be the same as when
all viewers press the button.

11
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,520
[No way]

12
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:51,510
Getting a vote from a judge would be so damaging.

13
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,420
[The unpredictable death match results]

14
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:57,580
A death match between
Yang Gyeong Hee and Park So Rang.

15
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:59,340
[Shocked]

16
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:00,420
[What's this?]

17
00:01:02,620 --> 00:01:05,040
[Director Yang Gyeong Hee won!]

18
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,660
A battle between friends who turned enemies.

19
00:01:07,660 --> 00:01:09,550
What could happen?

20
00:01:09,550 --> 00:01:11,730
[The Five Stars' votes widen the gap even more]

21
00:01:11,730 --> 00:01:15,840
The winner of this battle is
Director Han Sang Il.

22
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:21,200
Director Lee Joo Seung and Director Han Soo Ji.

23
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:24,660
["The Murderer Upstairs"]

24
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:28,250
[Lee Joo Seung gets three stops]

25
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:30,260
She's covering her mouth.

26
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:31,930
He did an amazing job.

27
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:34,670
I regretted picking him.

28
00:01:34,670 --> 00:01:37,090
I think it's about time I win.

29
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:41,750
[Who will be the winner of this death match?]

30
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:44,800
- What did you think, Director Han?
- She covered her mouth.

31
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:50,350
I'm a bit flustered because
he did such a good job.

32
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:54,300
[She is shocked by the quality
of his short drama]

33
00:01:54,300 --> 00:02:00,000
For her first teaser, didn't Director Han
get fewer than 10 stops, too?

34
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,100
Didn't she get five or something?

35
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:06,340
You survived cleanly
with five stops. Congratulations.

36
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:08,340
Thank you.

37
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:11,360
[What kind of result will her first
and second episodes bring?]

38
00:02:11,810 --> 00:02:13,660
I was so out of it.

39
00:02:13,660 --> 00:02:17,990
I went up there thinking this won't be easy.

40
00:02:17,990 --> 00:02:23,700
You have Shin Ye Eun in your short drama, right?

41
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:26,570
She'll probably appear again, right?

42
00:02:26,570 --> 00:02:29,190
Yes, even though she's very busy,

43
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:36,100
she came by because she wanted
to help. I was so grateful.

44
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:39,130
[Showing up with high energy]

45
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:42,530
[Director Han Soo Ji's trusty support]

46
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:46,330
Hello, long time no see.

47
00:02:46,330 --> 00:02:49,840
Hello, I'm playing Ji Yun Ju
in "Snakes and Ladders."

48
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,090
I'm Shin Ye Eun. Nice to meet you.

49
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:57,980
She's the one who allowed me
to be where I am now.

50
00:02:57,980 --> 00:02:59,510
[Shin Ye Eun reunites
with Han Soo Ji on Director's Arena]

51
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:01,930
- How much did you read?
- I read the whole thing.

52
00:03:01,930 --> 00:03:05,050
[Shin Ye Eun read the script for all 50 episodes]

53
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:07,190
- Action.
- Let go.

54
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:10,380
[Passionate acting]

55
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:14,170
[Yun Ju is about to get swallowed by a snake]

56
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:17,530
Cut. Let's go one more time.

57
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,470
[The director doesn't miss even
the smallest facial expressions]

58
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,820
It was a little lacking.

59
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:26,260
[The meeting of a passionate director and actress]

60
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:28,210
Yes, looks good.

61
00:03:28,210 --> 00:03:31,390
It's great. Nice, nice.

62
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:33,650
Say a word to Director Han.

63
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:35,550
[Director Han Soo Ji shows up]

64
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:39,290
I'm sending you a message. You can't be here.

65
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:40,980
[Embarrassed]

66
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:43,250
She's a director I want to work with more.

67
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:46,950
She makes me want to run to her wherever she is.

68
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:49,660
She's someone I trust a lot.

69
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:54,270
I'm so grateful to join her
for this great opportunity.

70
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:56,700
I hope Director's Arena is a huge success

71
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:59,820
and Director Han wins. Fighting.

72
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:02,110
Love you, Director Han.

73
00:04:03,270 --> 00:04:07,250
My job is to excel in directing.

74
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:09,680
I think making it look visually appealing

75
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:14,320
and showing more of my style is what I can do.

76
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:17,930
[How did "Snakes and Ladders" turn out?]

77
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:23,770
You showed us surprising
scenes using AI last time.

78
00:04:23,770 --> 00:04:26,950
Can we expect something even bigger this time?

79
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:29,250
Actually, Episodes 1 and 2 are about

80
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:35,290
how they got inside the old board
game called "Snakes and Ladders."

81
00:04:35,290 --> 00:04:41,820
The dramatic AI scenes begin
in Episode 3, when the game begins.

82
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:43,990
So, I'm a bit scared right now.

83
00:04:43,990 --> 00:04:47,490
The teaser showed scenes to hook you in.

84
00:04:47,490 --> 00:04:54,360
But the first two episodes are
about how they got inside the game.

85
00:04:54,360 --> 00:05:01,030
The episodes help viewers
understand the story's goal.

86
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:03,470
We'll start the judging now.

87
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,200
On the count of three, the video will start.

88
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,640
You can start voting as soon as the video starts.

89
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:11,370
We'll get started now.

90
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:18,080
I know Director Han Soo Ji is very good, but

91
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,480
it will be hard to beat three stops.

92
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:23,080
But what if she receives zero stops?

93
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:27,410
[Dark horse Lee Joo Seung
or the dependable Han Soo Ji?]

94
00:05:27,940 --> 00:05:29,690
Please have a quick look at this.

95
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:32,200
Please have a look. Please have a look just once.

96
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,260
Have a look at it just once. Thank you.

97
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:39,100
My sister disappeared from
this school three months ago.

98
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,800
She's either missing or murdered.

99
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:45,290
- Please have a look.
- But the school went silent.

100
00:05:45,290 --> 00:05:48,280
The prime suspect...

101
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,570
[This scene was filmed safely under the
professional film crew's supervision]

102
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,420
Hey, it's him, isn't it?

103
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:58,660
- That murderer?
- Daebak.

104
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:01,370
He was free without charges.

105
00:06:01,370 --> 00:06:04,290
[Maintaining zero stops so far]

106
00:06:04,290 --> 00:06:06,820
[Will it be as expected?]

107
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:09,270
[Nervous, anxious]

108
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:12,710
Nam Wu Min!

109
00:06:26,930 --> 00:06:28,460
Where is my sister?

110
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:31,480
Where is she, you murdering bastard?

111
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:35,390
[Three months ago]

112
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,000
[The stop count is rising]

113
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:47,110
[Quickly went up to three stops]

114
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:52,440
[Got as many stops as Lee Joo Seung
in the middle of Episode 1]

115
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:54,990
So pretty. So pretty.

116
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:56,460
Ji Yun Ju.

117
00:06:57,990 --> 00:06:59,120
What's the deal?

118
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,130
Why did you want to see me here?

119
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:03,690
I found out what the missing
kids share in common.

120
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,130
Too slow. Too slow.

121
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:08,880
They stayed in this basement
before they went missing.

122
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:10,720
Then, is this...

123
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:13,790
You know, too, right?

124
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:21,920
[Already at seven stops]

125
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:24,460
[What do I do?]

126
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:26,680
[The end of Episode 1]

127
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,730
The setup is elaborate.

128
00:07:28,730 --> 00:07:30,870
She needs to explain the game,
"Snakes and Ladders," too.

129
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:32,070
It loses its intensity.

130
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:34,630
[Episode 2 plays]

131
00:07:36,050 --> 00:07:38,650
- Do you have evidence?
- It keeps going up.

132
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:41,930
- My gosh. My gosh!
- Where's proof that I killed her?

133
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:45,540
- It was you. You killed her!
- It's going up that much?

134
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:50,310
Stop making a scene at my school.

135
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,820
Who are you? Get out of here.

136
00:07:53,570 --> 00:07:55,720
Get lost before I call the police.

137
00:07:58,590 --> 00:08:00,910
What are you doing? Leave.

138
00:08:02,030 --> 00:08:05,040
[The stop count is rising nonstop]

139
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:09,200
I wanted it to be similar, but I totally failed.

140
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,130
I felt so hurt.

141
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:12,820
This high?

142
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:14,330
I like it.

143
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:16,430
You have to sit through this much.

144
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,990
The opponent is too powerful.

145
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:34,020
You must be Yun Jeong.

146
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,090
Who are you?

147
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,660
I'm Cha Do Hun.

148
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:42,310
Should I help you with Yun Ju?

149
00:08:42,310 --> 00:08:44,430
Do you know my sister?

150
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:48,910
Wow, more than 50% voted.

151
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:51,110
Isn't that the highest so far?

152
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,910
10 o'clock at the old building's
basement. Nam Wu Min.

153
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:57,530
I saw her the day she went missing.

154
00:08:57,530 --> 00:09:01,320
I saw Nam Wu Min and Yun Ju
near the old building's basement.

155
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:04,350
- Let go.
- Shut up and follow me.

156
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:07,080
- Where are you going?
- I said follow me!

157
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:13,910
The last location written in the diary.

158
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:18,640
This is the only place
where I can find her trace.

159
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:21,850
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

160
00:09:21,850 --> 00:09:24,730
- Gosh.
- My gosh.

161
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:27,300
There is no AI in Episodes 1 and 2.

162
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:30,200
Director Han Soo Ji's video ended.

163
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:35,450
She received 31 stops from the viewers.

164
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,320
This creates a huge gap.

165
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:43,040
But we never know. The Five Stars
enjoyed Director Lee's,

166
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:46,510
but if we all voted, the score might change.

167
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:51,300
Director Lee Byeong Heon might've
thought the cinematographer was no good.

168
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,700
There could be a twist like that.

169
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:57,490
I think Director Han was ambitious.

170
00:09:57,490 --> 00:10:01,100
She considered the later episodes

171
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:06,790
and told the stories she wanted
to tell in the first two episodes.

172
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:10,160
- I wonder what that did.
- For Director Han Soo Ji,

173
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,570
the first two episodes were too slow.

174
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,330
I was hoping to see something more.

175
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:18,500
I think you were a bit too ambitious.

176
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:23,280
I wonder if being on the Director's Arena

177
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:26,410
made our brains a bit tired.

178
00:10:26,410 --> 00:10:28,810
I actually watched it feeling relaxed.

179
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:32,720
The acting was very good,
and the story was easy to follow.

180
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:35,240
I think it was well-made.

181
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:41,900
But it would've felt more like
a short drama if it were shorter.

182
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,720
Everyone's hopes were too high after the teaser.

183
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,190
The teaser was too powerful.

184
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:50,710
Director's Arena, Round 3, death match.

185
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:55,810
Director Lee Joo Seung is
far ahead by a big margin.

186
00:10:55,810 --> 00:11:01,020
But the result can change
depending on Five Stars' votes.

187
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:04,390
I'll reveal the final results.

188
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:08,140
Will there be a twist?

189
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,760
The results are...

190
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:16,000
The winner of this battle is...

191
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,620
The results are...

192
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:24,600
The winner of this battle is
Director Lee Joo Seung. Congratulations.

193
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:27,020
[Disappointed]

194
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:30,680
None of us pressed the button.

195
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:37,260
Director Lee is advancing to the next
round with 3 stops versus 51 stops.

196
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:40,900
The mission is to beat Lee Joo Seung now.

197
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:45,080
There are many dark horses, as you said.

198
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,710
I know.

199
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:49,970
How do you feel, Director Lee?

200
00:11:49,970 --> 00:11:53,080
I thought I'd lose the
entire time I was shooting.

201
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:59,020
I told the crew not to get high hopes
because my opponent is so strong.

202
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:01,280
But I'm happy that I got to win.

203
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:04,100
- I'm happy. Thank you.
- It must be disappointing.

204
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:06,670
How do you feel, Director Han Soo Ji?

205
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:12,360
I know, it's disappointing.
A lot of fun things happen later.

206
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:16,710
I guess the snake should've appeared
in the first two episodes, too.

207
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:22,710
The viewers had clear expectations
for "Snakes and Ladders."

208
00:12:22,710 --> 00:12:26,650
But I think I failed to satisfy them.

209
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:30,080
I got Director Han Soo Ji to finally lose.

210
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:34,600
I think I was happy about that.

211
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:38,670
Wow, he's such a dark horse.

212
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:41,610
- That was a clear win.
- Joo Seung totally did it.

213
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:46,040
- The former actors are amazing.
- Same with Yoo Jin.

214
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:49,580
We knew about Yoo Jin, but now it's Joo Seung.

215
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:53,140
He must have worked hard on the storyboard.

216
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:56,110
It was more of a movie than a short drama.

217
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,840
[The fate-determining death match continues]

218
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:02,540
It's a battle between two
international short drama directors.

219
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:05,380
"Medical Genius" got about 20 million views.

220
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:08,070
It was a top show of the week.

221
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:14,000
I'm a director, and I've directed
and produced over 20 short-form dramas.

222
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,290
[Two directors with international recognition]

223
00:13:16,290 --> 00:13:19,050
[What fates will they face in the death match?]

224
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:23,560
Director Lee Dong Hun chose
Director Yun Hyeong Shik.

225
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:25,860
He said he doesn't remember his teaser,

226
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:29,910
but he seemed confident.

227
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,620
Director Yun Hyeong Shik,

228
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:35,890
are you confident that he won't say
"forgettable" this time?

229
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:38,160
Yes, I am.

230
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,380
I'll make you forget yours with mine.

231
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:42,230
[Is that how it is?]

232
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:45,890
I'll prove that I survived because I'm powerful.

233
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:47,150
[Is there more?]

234
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:52,550
I hope this is your last time on the stage.

235
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:54,610
I thought he worked for a funeral company.

236
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:56,380
It was like he was sending him away.

237
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:59,110
The death match starts now.

238
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:00,630
[Director Yun Hyeong Shik goes first]

239
00:14:00,630 --> 00:14:03,290
Director Yun Hyeong Shik will go first.

240
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:05,070
[He seems confident]

241
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:10,750
You say you've been waiting for a death match.

242
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:19,610
I wasn't able to show my style
in the first two missions.

243
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:22,790
I'll be okay even if I get eliminated.

244
00:14:22,790 --> 00:14:25,610
I'm satisfied with the outcome.

245
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:30,790
People usually get good results
by following their guts.

246
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:35,350
Director Yun Hyeong Shik's
"Re:Debut - How to Debut from Death."

247
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:36,960
Tell us what to focus on.

248
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:42,030
I've been explaining my work
in the past two rounds.

249
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:47,290
But I think my verbal skills raised
the expectations too much.

250
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:51,600
So, I'm trying to say less,
but I prepared a gift for you.

251
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,890
- What is it?
- You'll see a familiar face later.

252
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:56,400
Please focus on that.

253
00:14:56,400 --> 00:15:00,200
We don't know, either. Can't wait
for the surprise appearance.

254
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,470
We'll start the judging now.

255
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,500
[Worried about his gift]

256
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,180
I'm curious.

257
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:10,730
150,000 people apply to
become idol trainees per year.

258
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:13,620
But only 963 of them survive.

259
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:17,320
Today, another person failed to survive.

260
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,480
Do you have something to say?

261
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:20,780
Sir, it's been seven years.

262
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:22,470
Do you know how I've felt...

263
00:15:22,470 --> 00:15:25,940
[Oh, that's...]

264
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:27,840
[Lee Beom Gyu was the gift]

265
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,190
[Not getting reactions]

266
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:32,690
Do you know how I've felt all this time...

267
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:36,190
Kang Shi Yun, 24 years old.

268
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:39,320
He's been average throughout the
showcases and assessments.

269
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:44,940
He's not eye-catching, and he has
no potential to build a fan base.

270
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:47,170
You have no star potential.

271
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:50,330
Shi Yun, the agency doesn't
make your dream come true.

272
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:51,470
It's a place for making money.

273
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:53,960
You're 24. That's way too old.

274
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,290
You might as well be dead.

275
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:57,150
Sir, if you just let me debut...

276
00:15:57,150 --> 00:16:00,030
I'm kneeling right now. Please understand.

277
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,740
Shit!

278
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:08,020
Shit?

279
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:10,050
[Embarrassed]

280
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:13,600
- I'll return the gift.
- Since I've been on a diet,

281
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,210
I never got to drink alcohol.

282
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:19,880
I don't even have enough money to get drunk.

283
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,960
[The stop count is going up
as soon as the gift disappears]

284
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,970
[I should've used him more]

285
00:16:24,970 --> 00:16:26,720
I got my hair permed...

286
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:31,700
I used to practice all night just to debut.

287
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:37,850
Do I have to join a new management company?

288
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:40,060
Will they even accept me?

289
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,670
Is this how I die?

290
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:48,000
[Yun Hyeong Shik's "Re:Debut -
How to Debut from Death" Episode 2]

291
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:51,850
What? Why doesn't it hurt? Am I already dead?

292
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:56,900
This is when it floods in. He's in trouble.

293
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,670
[No]

294
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:01,990
I was taken aback that it went up
where I least expected it.

295
00:17:02,890 --> 00:17:10,000
The number went up where I thought
it was just getting interesting.

296
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,780
Am I already dead?

297
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,300
Huh?

298
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:20,180
Nice to meet you, Kang Shi Yun.

299
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:22,400
I'm Team Leader Ji Seon Wu
of the Death Transition Team

300
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,300
at Afterlife Management.

301
00:17:25,060 --> 00:17:28,020
Afterlife Management?

302
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:31,800
Am I really dead?

303
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,050
Yes, you're dead.

304
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:37,390
04:13. The cause of death is a car accident.

305
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:40,260
What are you talking about?
This is a dream, right?

306
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:44,210
[About to get votes from half of the viewers]

307
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:03,550
If you're finished, may I start talking?

308
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:05,840
You have two options, Mr. Kang.

309
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:09,410
One is the train you see behind you.

310
00:18:09,410 --> 00:18:11,920
It's a train to the afterlife.

311
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:15,510
You haven't committed a major sin
according to the record.

312
00:18:15,510 --> 00:18:16,490
[AI-generated footage]

313
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,180
What's the other option?

314
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:31,340
I offer you a conditional rebirth.

315
00:18:35,540 --> 00:18:38,580
[Finished playing
Director Yun's Episodes 1 and 2]

316
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:42,700
Director Yun Hyeong Shik's
video finished playing.

317
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:46,950
You received 32 stops from the viewers.

318
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:50,270
I think we need to talk
about the gift he mentioned.

319
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:52,150
By chance, was the gift...

320
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:54,290
Did we receive the wrong gift?

321
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:57,460
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have talked into the mic.

322
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:58,930
It was too...

323
00:18:58,930 --> 00:19:01,010
While I was watching it, I thought...

324
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:03,050
"That can't be the gift, right?"

325
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:06,000
- "Gift? I didn't ask for one."
- "There has to be something more, right?"

326
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,340
The one who got eliminated was the busiest.

327
00:19:09,340 --> 00:19:12,710
It was a good gift for my mother,
mother-in-law, and wife.

328
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:14,020
Thank you.

329
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:16,140
[How heartwarming]

330
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,850
[Critique time]

331
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:20,570
[What did the Five Stars think?]

332
00:19:20,570 --> 00:19:23,710
When the count went up,

333
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:28,330
I thought I wasn't the only one
who felt that way.

334
00:19:28,330 --> 00:19:30,480
The colors were so nice. The shot compositions

335
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:36,170
and the actors' emotions came through very well.

336
00:19:36,170 --> 00:19:38,470
I thought it was fun, but...

337
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:40,680
To explain that he's dead,

338
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:45,460
the Angel of Death kept
showing up in front of him.

339
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:49,860
Since this is a short drama,
you should have just shown it once

340
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:52,290
and moved on to the next scene.

341
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:55,290
I think that would've been better.

342
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:59,620
To put it simply, it was way too safe.

343
00:19:59,620 --> 00:20:06,040
I think it should've been
a minute and a half, not three minutes.

344
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:10,730
I brought the best product I could.

345
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:12,420
But critiques are supposed to be harsh.

346
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:15,780
The fact that many people
weren't satisfied with it

347
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:20,420
means I need to rewind
and look for its weak spots.

348
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:23,410
[Finished judging
Director Yun Hyeong Shik's work]

349
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:27,350
[It's Director Lee Dong Hun's turn to be judged]

350
00:20:27,350 --> 00:20:32,410
I heard you prepared for this
as if it were your last chance.

351
00:20:32,410 --> 00:20:35,630
I heard you worked very hard on it.

352
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:38,500
And you used all the connections you have.

353
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,980
Yes, I summoned everyone I know.

354
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:46,270
My elementary, middle, and high
school classmates appeared as extras.

355
00:20:46,270 --> 00:20:49,340
So did my old buddies from my film school years.

356
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:52,140
You really called everyone around you.

357
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:54,730
So far, it's a little unnerving. Who else?

358
00:20:54,730 --> 00:20:59,050
And a dentist I know also appeared.

359
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:01,990
[A very personal casting process]

360
00:21:01,990 --> 00:21:03,490
I hope everyone had fun.

361
00:21:03,490 --> 00:21:06,280
I cast many people.

362
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:09,620
Anyone else? Someone we might know?

363
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:14,440
Oh, yes. Amy also helped.

364
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:18,150
She joined us as the cast changed.

365
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:23,950
In Round 2, I saw that
Amy appeared as a hidden actor.

366
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:25,520
I've always been a fan,

367
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:29,410
and I thought she would be a perfect Ri Ah.

368
00:21:29,410 --> 00:21:34,170
I cast her, hoping to get the
winning director's energy.

369
00:21:34,170 --> 00:21:38,220
[Episodes 1 and 2 became stronger
with Amy joining the cast]

370
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:44,060
I think playing a chaebol with
an anger issue suits me well.

371
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:47,460
[Lee Dong Hun's "The Beggar Couple
Joins the Chaebol Family"]

372
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:49,860
It must be fast-paced and well-made.

373
00:21:49,860 --> 00:21:53,200
- He made 20 short dramas.
- He's a master.

374
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:55,460
[Nervous]

375
00:21:55,840 --> 00:22:01,270
I had more provocative and
engaging scenes in Episodes 1 and 2.

376
00:22:01,270 --> 00:22:05,300
I think I'll win.

377
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:10,130
["The Beggar Couple Joins the Chaebol Family"]

378
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:12,060
Come check out our goods.

379
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:13,320
Check out the puppies.

380
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:14,650
We'll give you a good price.

381
00:22:14,650 --> 00:22:16,590
My wife is almost due.

382
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:20,150
We'd appreciate it if you just buy one.

383
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:22,970
Puppy.

384
00:22:22,970 --> 00:22:24,420
Who said you can sell stuff here?

385
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:26,040
Do you want to die?

386
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,790
Please don't do this.

387
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:29,660
Some people hate stuff like that.

388
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:33,210
- Wow, it's skyrocketing.
- He's in trouble.

389
00:22:33,210 --> 00:22:35,810
[Got stop votes at the beginning of Episode 1]

390
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:37,980
[What's going on?]

391
00:22:37,980 --> 00:22:39,040
Who cares?

392
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:41,080
Just take your kid and die, then!

393
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:42,880
That's enough. We'll call the police.

394
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,950
- Police?
- Just give these to me.

395
00:22:44,950 --> 00:22:47,040
I'll buy them all.

396
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,030
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Thank you. Thank you.

397
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:51,080
Take all of them.

398
00:22:54,170 --> 00:22:55,470
They were acting.

399
00:22:55,470 --> 00:22:57,380
Your acting keeps on improving.

400
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,770
I added a bonus today.

401
00:22:58,770 --> 00:23:00,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

402
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,840
I'm sorry I pushed you too hard today.

403
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,220
It's okay.

404
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:06,580
It didn't hurt at all because of this pillow.

405
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:09,040
We'll see you tomorrow, then.

406
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,760
Yes, thank you!

407
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:14,420
- Hey, I made my rent!
- Come on...

408
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:18,960
I'm sick of making money like this.

409
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:21,510
How about we pull a big one?

410
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,440
Did you come here to eat?

411
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,020
But still, I'm hungry.

412
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:33,420
Don't you know how much the entrance fee costs?

413
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:37,790
Here, look. We just need to seduce one person.

414
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:39,850
You know her, right? She's the
daughter of the Ohga Group.

415
00:23:39,850 --> 00:23:41,430
She's the owner of this hotel.

416
00:23:41,430 --> 00:23:43,850
- Really?
- Should I try seducing her?

417
00:23:43,850 --> 00:23:45,910
Would someone like her even look at you?

418
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:48,730
You just need to help me a little.

419
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:51,420
[Lee Dong Hun's "The Beggar Couple
Joins the Chaebol Family" Episode 2]

420
00:23:51,420 --> 00:23:53,020
Thank you.

421
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:56,840
You look so cute today.

422
00:24:06,530 --> 00:24:09,630
My goodness. I'm sorry.

423
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,940
The wine disappeared.

424
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:13,810
We got a continuity issue.

425
00:24:13,810 --> 00:24:15,000
- What?
- Huh?

426
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,210
Isn't that too noticeable?

427
00:24:22,790 --> 00:24:25,830
My goodness. I'm sorry.

428
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:28,090
- I'm a little drunk.
- Are your eyes for decoration?

429
00:24:28,090 --> 00:24:30,250
You ruined my dress!

430
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:36,110
Are you okay?

431
00:24:36,110 --> 00:24:39,060
- Apologize.
- She bumped into me, too.

432
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,920
Why should I?

433
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:44,520
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

434
00:24:46,180 --> 00:24:47,420
I was panicking.

435
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:49,970
People suddenly started clicking like crazy.

436
00:24:49,970 --> 00:24:53,330
Once it started, it wouldn't stop.

437
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,940
- Apologize.
- She bumped into me, too.

438
00:24:59,940 --> 00:25:00,890
Why should I?

439
00:25:00,890 --> 00:25:04,620
You ruined the day for the
most beautiful person here.

440
00:25:04,620 --> 00:25:06,630
Of course, you should apologize.

441
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:09,180
Well, I'm sorry.

442
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,670
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

443
00:25:16,670 --> 00:25:20,200
I haven't seen you before.
Where did you come from?

444
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:30,540
Learning that might hurt you.

445
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:35,450
Cut. No? There's more?

446
00:25:35,450 --> 00:25:36,590
It's getting dangerous.

447
00:25:36,590 --> 00:25:38,130
It's dangerous.

448
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:42,850
It pisses me off the more I think about it.

449
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:46,250
He gets to play a cool guy all by himself.

450
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:49,310
A beggar can't keep pretending to be rich.

451
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:53,010
- Whoa, whoa.
- You'll have to leave this party.

452
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:54,250
Let go of me.

453
00:25:54,250 --> 00:25:55,710
Don't you know who she is?

454
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:58,440
I didn't mean to do that.

455
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,560
Let go.

456
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:01,710
- Come with me.
- What's going on?

457
00:26:02,380 --> 00:26:05,340
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

458
00:26:06,510 --> 00:26:08,680
[Serious]

459
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:12,630
I didn't think I'd get so many votes.

460
00:26:12,630 --> 00:26:15,300
It was such a shocking result.

461
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:20,040
I was surprised to see his result, too.

462
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:23,240
He got more votes than I expected.

463
00:26:25,330 --> 00:26:28,560
Director Lee Dong Hun's video ended.

464
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:33,430
- It's so neck and neck.
- You got 30 stops from the viewers.

465
00:26:33,430 --> 00:26:38,580
I kept wondering who your
classmates and the dentist were.

466
00:26:38,580 --> 00:26:41,110
Seriously. Which ones were they?

467
00:26:41,110 --> 00:26:44,660
My classmates were fired for poor acting.

468
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:47,100
That was an issue.

469
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:48,890
[Why did he bring it up, then?]

470
00:26:48,890 --> 00:26:50,520
[Sorry, buddies]

471
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:53,380
This battle was...

472
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:56,420
- How could it be so neck and neck?
- They're two votes apart.

473
00:26:56,420 --> 00:27:00,170
Isn't this the closest one so far?

474
00:27:00,170 --> 00:27:02,860
[What is their fate?]

475
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:06,850
When the votes suddenly went up, I wondered

476
00:27:06,850 --> 00:27:09,440
if it were too similar to other short dramas.

477
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:12,850
I feel like that's why the count went up.

478
00:27:12,850 --> 00:27:15,600
It didn't feel new at all.

479
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:19,740
I'd work with him if I were a producer.

480
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:22,950
It met the requirements of a hit short drama.

481
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:27,980
I think you made appropriate
choices for a short drama.

482
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:32,310
It checked all the boxes in that regard.

483
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:36,720
I was like, "I want to work with that person."

484
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:40,160
"Extreme Job" and "Twenty"
are my favorite movies.

485
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,860
Director Lee Byeong Heon...

486
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:43,670
This is heartwarming.

487
00:27:43,670 --> 00:27:47,300
That's why I wanted to add
the Korean-style comedy.

488
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:50,700
- It was very addictive and...
- That's enough.

489
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:53,140
What did you think, Director Lee Hwan?

490
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:57,900
I thought it was like
a typical Chinese short drama.

491
00:27:57,900 --> 00:28:01,890
It felt like he cranked it out
following the formula.

492
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:07,960
It was probably disappointing to the viewers.

493
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:10,920
Let's check the results, then.

494
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:14,270
Director Yun Hyeong Shik has
32 stops from the viewers.

495
00:28:14,270 --> 00:28:17,590
And Director Lee Dong Hun has 30.

496
00:28:17,590 --> 00:28:23,880
Director Lee Dong Hun is
slightly ahead right now.

497
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:27,580
Will this solidify the result,
or will there be a twist?

498
00:28:27,580 --> 00:28:33,150
I'll reveal the final results,
including the Five Stars' votes.

499
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:34,590
Okay...

500
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:38,100
It's just a two-vote difference.

501
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:41,010
It's totally up to us.

502
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:45,990
Who will be the winner of this battle?

503
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:49,410
Please reveal the final results.

504
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:56,310
[Director Lee Dong Hun wins]

505
00:28:56,310 --> 00:29:00,920
Director Lee Dong Hun
is the winner of this battle.

506
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,880
[They got the same number
of votes from the Five Stars]

507
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:05,920
[Nerve-racking until the last minute]

508
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:09,480
[They both got votes from three Five Stars]

509
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:11,100
How could this be?

510
00:29:11,100 --> 00:29:12,940
It was so neck and neck.

511
00:29:12,940 --> 00:29:14,320
Seriously.

512
00:29:15,300 --> 00:29:17,940
Gosh, that was a close one.

513
00:29:17,940 --> 00:29:19,820
I think I need to accept the result.

514
00:29:19,820 --> 00:29:22,900
I feel like I learned a lot.

515
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:26,540
I won't think of this
as the end of the road for me.

516
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:28,000
I'll continue.

517
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:32,090
I feel like I just barely made it.

518
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:36,190
I think this means I need to work harder.

519
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:39,540
I was like, "If only I had one more
person on my side."

520
00:29:39,540 --> 00:29:44,420
Because we both received three votes
from the Five Stars.

521
00:29:45,190 --> 00:29:49,390
If I could have changed
a couple of people's minds,

522
00:29:49,390 --> 00:29:52,660
I thought the result could have been different.

523
00:29:53,340 --> 00:29:55,800
A battle on the edge of the cliff.

524
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,270
1:1 death match.

525
00:29:57,270 --> 00:30:02,280
Next, we have a seasoned director
and a high-spirited new director.

526
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:04,390
It's true. A seasoned director.

527
00:30:04,390 --> 00:30:07,060
- "Seasoned" puts too much pressure.
- But you are.

528
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:08,540
[He's anxious]

529
00:30:09,050 --> 00:30:12,040
[A battle between two survival rom-coms]

530
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:14,770
I've made long-form dramas before,

531
00:30:14,770 --> 00:30:17,470
but now, I want to pivot to short-form dramas.

532
00:30:17,470 --> 00:30:20,330
I took a long break from directing.

533
00:30:20,330 --> 00:30:22,900
But it's something I still want to do.

534
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:25,720
I had been desperate, and I came
across this great opportunity.

535
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:31,370
I feel so excited to be back on set.

536
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:34,090
For the first time, we have zero stops.

537
00:30:34,090 --> 00:30:38,710
You survived cleanly, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

538
00:30:38,710 --> 00:30:40,790
[He took first place in Round 2 as well]

539
00:30:41,420 --> 00:30:44,540
[Director Lee Yoo Jin has been forging ahead]

540
00:30:44,950 --> 00:30:47,520
[A potential winner vs. A desperate director]

541
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:51,650
- This battle will be very...
- It'll be fun.

542
00:30:51,650 --> 00:30:54,860
- It'll get bloody.
- I'm most excited about this one.

543
00:30:54,860 --> 00:30:56,970
What do you think, Director Lee Yoo Jin?

544
00:30:56,970 --> 00:30:58,640
What were you thinking when you chose him?

545
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:01,440
Because you thought you could beat him?

546
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:03,210
Yes.

547
00:31:03,210 --> 00:31:05,670
[Short and strong]

548
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:08,850
Do you still feel the same way?

549
00:31:08,850 --> 00:31:10,140
Yes.

550
00:31:10,870 --> 00:31:12,790
Wow, scary.

551
00:31:12,790 --> 00:31:14,910
[Death Match is scary]

552
00:31:14,910 --> 00:31:17,720
They say, "There's nothing to eat at a big party."

553
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,540
[Feeling attacked]

554
00:31:19,540 --> 00:31:23,880
- We got "Show Me the Money" here.
- I heard so many good things about him.

555
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:31,540
I hope the big party also
has a table full of food.

556
00:31:31,540 --> 00:31:33,600
This is getting fun.

557
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:37,200
We'll watch Director Go Hyeon Guk's first.

558
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:42,790
Did you return to a film set in three years?

559
00:31:42,790 --> 00:31:45,710
Yes. The last time I directed
was three years ago.

560
00:31:45,710 --> 00:31:47,790
How did you feel?

561
00:31:47,790 --> 00:31:50,910
It was emotional for me.

562
00:31:53,090 --> 00:31:56,630
I was reminded that it's a job
that involves so many people.

563
00:31:56,630 --> 00:32:00,220
I thought, "Right, that's how it was."

564
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:06,080
I heard you cast the female lead
by sending her a DM.

565
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:08,820
- How did you hear about her?
- I'm curious, too. How did you?

566
00:32:08,820 --> 00:32:11,860
I was impressed with her acting in

567
00:32:11,860 --> 00:32:15,060
"Blood Strangers" on Lehzin Snack.

568
00:32:15,060 --> 00:32:16,570
Her name is Song Ha Jin.

569
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:19,350
I thought the role suited her so well.

570
00:32:19,350 --> 00:32:21,170
Without embellishing things,

571
00:32:21,170 --> 00:32:24,940
I sent her a DM saying,
"I'm Go Hyeon Guk, who's directing

572
00:32:24,940 --> 00:32:26,570
'Can't Live Without Dopamine Spikes.'"

573
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:30,040
I sent her my phone number,
saying I'd like to cast her.

574
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:32,730
And I got a message from her.

575
00:32:32,730 --> 00:32:36,570
I guess you have to keep things simple
to avoid sounding like a scammer.

576
00:32:36,570 --> 00:32:38,930
Right, you can't embellish too much.

577
00:32:38,930 --> 00:32:40,870
If he mentioned his experience,

578
00:32:40,870 --> 00:32:44,570
she would've been like,
"Why are you sending me this?"

579
00:32:44,570 --> 00:32:48,110
- I was glad she didn't think I was a weirdo.
- Right.

580
00:32:48,110 --> 00:32:50,130
[She joined the set after the DM]

581
00:32:50,130 --> 00:32:52,280
I'm just grateful.

582
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:54,400
[Likewise]

583
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,720
Thank you.

584
00:32:55,720 --> 00:33:03,020
At first, I was like,
"This is how he's contacting me?"

585
00:33:03,020 --> 00:33:06,010
I read the script he sent me.

586
00:33:06,010 --> 00:33:10,630
It was so refreshing and fun.

587
00:33:10,630 --> 00:33:13,230
She asked me who wrote it
when she came to the table-read.

588
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:16,140
I asked who wrote it, and he said, "I did."

589
00:33:16,140 --> 00:33:18,490
And I was like, "Really?"

590
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:23,530
You're leaving the office.
Take big steps like this.

591
00:33:23,530 --> 00:33:26,840
[What's the story that got Song Ha Jin hooked?]

592
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:29,310
The female lead is a drama writer.

593
00:33:29,310 --> 00:33:32,420
A production company rejects
her script, calling it boring.

594
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:34,580
On the way back, she gets into an accident.

595
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:39,730
And she ends up inside the boring
long-form drama she wrote.

596
00:33:39,730 --> 00:33:43,430
That world is about to collapse
because it lacks dopamine points.

597
00:33:43,430 --> 00:33:48,520
She ruins her own work to survive in this world.

598
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:53,340
My short drama is critical of short dramas.

599
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:54,980
[How refreshing]

600
00:33:54,980 --> 00:33:57,110
After you watch this drama,

601
00:33:57,110 --> 00:34:01,140
I hope it gives you something to think about

602
00:34:01,140 --> 00:34:04,450
in terms of the short drama itself.

603
00:34:04,450 --> 00:34:06,860
Wow, I'm curious.

604
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:09,270
- It's critical of short dramas?
- A short drama that's critical of itself?

605
00:34:09,270 --> 00:34:11,380
How will he criticize them?

606
00:34:11,380 --> 00:34:13,620
[His opponent is more nervous than he is]

607
00:34:18,570 --> 00:34:20,760
I don't like short-form dramas.

608
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,510
A man and a woman meet in a minute.

609
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:24,840
They slam each other on the wall and kiss.

610
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:26,700
There are no characters and no story.

611
00:34:26,700 --> 00:34:29,950
All it does is spike dopamine.

612
00:34:31,370 --> 00:34:33,280
Forget the story structure.

613
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:36,440
A world that goes crazy over provocation.

614
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,350
What's this?

615
00:34:38,350 --> 00:34:40,540
She's doing that right now.

616
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:43,260
But...

617
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:46,520
I'm doing this to survive.

618
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:47,880
That's right.

619
00:34:48,530 --> 00:34:53,980
The Intern's ASMR that will put
a cranky chairman to sleep.

620
00:34:53,980 --> 00:34:56,320
"A 2 a.m. Serenade"!

621
00:34:56,900 --> 00:34:59,250
What do you think? It's my best work yet.

622
00:34:59,250 --> 00:35:01,020
Jae Mi, it's not fun*.
("Jaemi" means "fun" in Korean)

623
00:35:01,020 --> 00:35:02,620
It's not fun or charming.

624
00:35:02,620 --> 00:35:04,980
It's not refreshing, either. It's just no fun.

625
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:06,020
Plain and simple.

626
00:35:06,020 --> 00:35:09,440
Can you come up with a spicy short
drama that wakes you right up?

627
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,700
That's not a drama-

628
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:14,260
Bring something that spikes
dopamine within a minute.

629
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:16,450
Seriously.

630
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:24,520
My childhood friend became a top star.

631
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:27,420
But I'm getting yelled at on the streets.

632
00:35:27,420 --> 00:35:30,330
I cried reading this. It was so moving.

633
00:35:30,330 --> 00:35:32,900
- Really?
- Yes. So, keep at it.

634
00:35:32,900 --> 00:35:35,500
I'll play the lead someday.

635
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:37,310
Min Do Pa.

636
00:35:37,310 --> 00:35:39,650
- Min Do Pa?
- Wait until I write a masterpiece.

637
00:35:39,650 --> 00:35:43,760
I'm sorry I couldn't keep the promise.

638
00:35:51,010 --> 00:35:54,220
[Episode 1 ended with just six stops]

639
00:35:54,220 --> 00:35:56,380
[Calm]

640
00:35:56,380 --> 00:35:59,170
[Getting increasingly anxious]

641
00:35:59,170 --> 00:36:00,600
[Go Hyeon Guk's "Can't Live
Without Dopamine Spikes" Episode 2]

642
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:03,230
What? I'm sure I got hit by a car.

643
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:05,380
Taesan Group?

644
00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:08,570
Am I inside the drama I wrote?

645
00:36:11,980 --> 00:36:14,700
What's happening to my face?

646
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:19,830
You're an extra in a no-fun drama,
"A 2 a.m. Serenade."

647
00:36:19,830 --> 00:36:23,280
The world instantly disappears
if the dopamine point reaches zero.

648
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:25,090
[Totally into it]

649
00:36:25,090 --> 00:36:27,530
She's trying to survive?

650
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:29,380
I see, she's trying to survive.

651
00:36:29,380 --> 00:36:31,690
[The stop count froze at six]

652
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:34,760
Instantly disappears?

653
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:40,630
[Taesan Group's Chairman Cha Do Jin]

654
00:36:40,630 --> 00:36:42,120
Min Do Pa?

655
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:45,600
- Do Pa.
- Oh, no.

656
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:47,040
Gosh...

657
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:50,910
Are you looking down on me because I'm an extra?

658
00:36:51,650 --> 00:36:55,460
Assert yourself to the male lead
and earn dopamine points.

659
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:58,620
The remaining points are 60 points. 59 points.

660
00:36:58,620 --> 00:37:00,360
No, hurry!

661
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:01,720
What's wrong with my hands?

662
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,620
I'll die at this rate. I need to do something.

663
00:37:05,270 --> 00:37:08,800
Bring something that spikes dopamine.

664
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,120
Fine.

665
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:13,570
I'll ruin my drama with my own hands.

666
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:17,070
I don't like short-form dramas.

667
00:37:17,070 --> 00:37:22,620
But I'm doing this to survive.

668
00:37:27,180 --> 00:37:28,730
[Dopamine spiking]

669
00:37:28,730 --> 00:37:30,590
[LOL]

670
00:37:30,590 --> 00:37:32,530
[Satisfied]

671
00:37:32,530 --> 00:37:34,720
[It's getting good reactions]

672
00:37:36,340 --> 00:37:38,040
He became a new man.

673
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,620
I thought it was fun, too.

674
00:37:40,620 --> 00:37:42,720
It was well crafted.

675
00:37:43,350 --> 00:37:45,460
I thought I was in trouble.

676
00:37:49,150 --> 00:37:50,680
Dopamine explosion.

677
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:54,300
The male lead will acknowledge your face.

678
00:37:54,300 --> 00:37:58,370
Who are you, and why are you
making that face in front of me?

679
00:38:00,660 --> 00:38:03,200
[Leading with 15 stops from the viewers]

680
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:04,610
[The reaction is explosive]

681
00:38:04,610 --> 00:38:06,740
Wow, that was so refreshing.

682
00:38:06,740 --> 00:38:09,410
Director Go Hyeon Guk,

683
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:11,210
you've finally adjusted.

684
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:16,140
- He got adjusted to short dramas.
- It's a new method.

685
00:38:16,140 --> 00:38:18,170
[The directors are talking, too]

686
00:38:18,170 --> 00:38:19,380
That was good.

687
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:20,710
That was fun.

688
00:38:20,710 --> 00:38:23,450
I didn't know it was already Episode 2.

689
00:38:24,140 --> 00:38:25,780
His experience sure does count.

690
00:38:26,820 --> 00:38:28,900
I got strangely sucked in.

691
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:32,890
When you said it was a short drama
critical of itself, I loved that selling point.

692
00:38:32,890 --> 00:38:39,060
I love the idea that her stressful
situation dictates the story, too.

693
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:44,580
[The narration and the story
reflect her situation]

694
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:48,570
Of all the short dramas we saw
on Director's Arena thus far,

695
00:38:48,570 --> 00:38:51,870
this was my absolute favorite.

696
00:38:51,870 --> 00:38:57,430
Hoping to see a drama like this,

697
00:38:57,430 --> 00:39:00,320
I decided to participate in the Director's Arena.

698
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:04,910
It fit my criteria perfectly.

699
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:10,160
Director Lee Yoo Jin finally has a rival.

700
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:11,890
He found his match.

701
00:39:11,890 --> 00:39:15,200
I feel like it won't be easy.

702
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:20,290
The people who pressed the stop button early on

703
00:39:20,290 --> 00:39:23,860
have no choice but to watch the
whole thing because of our system.

704
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:28,110
I think those people probably regretted it.

705
00:39:28,110 --> 00:39:30,970
"Did I press it too soon?
This is better than I thought."

706
00:39:30,970 --> 00:39:32,540
They agree.

707
00:39:32,540 --> 00:39:39,190
I think some people might have
hoped they could cancel it.

708
00:39:39,190 --> 00:39:42,410
It got more engaging as it progressed.

709
00:39:42,410 --> 00:39:48,400
The story got me thinking, "Huh? Look at this."

710
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:52,380
Is there someone like that
who's willing to be interviewed?

711
00:39:52,380 --> 00:39:53,840
Yes, Director.

712
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:57,230
I pressed it in the billboard scene.

713
00:39:57,230 --> 00:39:59,530
[Toward the latter half of Episode 1]

714
00:40:00,950 --> 00:40:01,960
[Stop]

715
00:40:03,130 --> 00:40:05,480
But it got so good after that.

716
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,870
I'm so sorry.

717
00:40:06,870 --> 00:40:08,420
[I knew it]

718
00:40:08,420 --> 00:40:10,120
I'm very sorry.

719
00:40:10,120 --> 00:40:12,860
He could've gotten 14 stops.

720
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:16,740
[Maybe I shouldn't have talked]

721
00:40:16,740 --> 00:40:19,000
[Will Director Eun Jong Hun's
vote change his fate?]

722
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:23,700
I thought Yoo Jin must be feeling nervous.

723
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:28,790
Director Lee Yoo Jin, please come forward.

724
00:40:28,790 --> 00:40:33,350
You got to see Director Go Hyeon Guk's.
What did you think?

725
00:40:33,350 --> 00:40:35,640
To be honest,

726
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:37,290
I enjoyed it.

727
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:42,540
You looked so unhappy coming up on the stage.

728
00:40:42,540 --> 00:40:46,350
[Worried]

729
00:40:47,430 --> 00:40:50,310
I've been nervous and worried this whole time.

730
00:40:50,310 --> 00:40:54,800
I am grateful that he did his best.

731
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:57,260
I did my best as well.

732
00:40:57,900 --> 00:40:59,300
You must've felt threatened.

733
00:40:59,300 --> 00:41:02,940
I heard you changed the scene order, too.

734
00:41:02,940 --> 00:41:04,050
Not just the poster.

735
00:41:04,050 --> 00:41:08,640
I placed the exciting scenes toward the front.

736
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:11,230
I changed the order.

737
00:41:11,230 --> 00:41:15,860
[First shooting day of
"Cast Them If You See the Path"]

738
00:41:16,460 --> 00:41:18,410
I think it's okay.

739
00:41:18,410 --> 00:41:21,940
[Trying to look young in a school uniform]

740
00:41:21,940 --> 00:41:26,340
I'm in a school uniform at my age.

741
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,900
I'm sorry.

742
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:31,900
But I can do what I want.

743
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:33,720
Because this is my series.

744
00:41:34,490 --> 00:41:37,020
[Putting on the necktie]

745
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:42,850
[Director/actor Lee Yoo Jin is ready]

746
00:41:42,850 --> 00:41:46,400
I didn't get a wink of sleep.

747
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:49,480
I had to work on the storyboard.

748
00:41:50,370 --> 00:41:54,200
[A rumor says you changed everything]

749
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:58,590
Since the final mission is a death match,

750
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:01,570
it'll be a battle of dopamine.

751
00:42:01,570 --> 00:42:08,030
I thought showing the kiss scene
early on was a good strategy.

752
00:42:08,030 --> 00:42:10,250
Brush your teeth, Gyeong Eun.

753
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,870
- I already brushed them.
- You did?

754
00:42:12,870 --> 00:42:14,490
How about you brush them again?

755
00:42:15,290 --> 00:42:17,110
I'm out of toothpaste.

756
00:42:17,110 --> 00:42:19,140
- Who has toothpaste?
- I do.

757
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:22,090
[The female lead is sharing her toothpaste]

758
00:42:22,090 --> 00:42:25,190
- More, more.
- More? How hard will you brush them?

759
00:42:25,190 --> 00:42:27,260
[Plenty]

760
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:34,480
This is the bare minimum of etiquette.

761
00:42:34,480 --> 00:42:37,120
[Pros make sure to get minty]

762
00:42:37,490 --> 00:42:40,360
[Starting the shoot feeling refreshed]

763
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:42,240
[Heart fluttering]

764
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:44,270
[Romantic gaze]

765
00:42:46,740 --> 00:42:48,530
[Cut!]

766
00:42:48,530 --> 00:42:50,870
[Switching to a director instantly]

