1023
00:56:04,510 --> 00:56:06,410
A fund to produce short-form drama.

1024
00:56:06,410 --> 00:56:09,500
The last battle to determine the final winner.

1025
00:56:09,500 --> 00:56:13,080
Korea's first-ever short drama directing
survival competition, Director's Arena.

1026
00:56:13,080 --> 00:56:15,930
The grand final round has started.

1027
00:56:17,250 --> 00:56:20,370
[Excited]

1028
00:56:20,370 --> 00:56:27,730
The final products that the directors poured
everything into will be revealed today.

1029
00:56:27,730 --> 00:56:33,090
We're already looking forward to the
stories that will capture our hearts.

1030
00:56:33,090 --> 00:56:36,490
Let's finish the race together today.

1031
00:56:37,560 --> 00:56:40,500
[Excited]

1032
00:56:41,350 --> 00:56:44,790
Please welcome the contenders
who advanced to the final

1033
00:56:44,790 --> 00:56:47,820
after surviving the death match.

1034
00:56:47,820 --> 00:56:51,230
[The survivors who made it
through the hellish round]

1035
00:56:51,230 --> 00:56:53,110
The winners.

1036
00:56:53,110 --> 00:56:57,590
I'm curious how you feel
about entering the final round.

1037
00:56:57,590 --> 00:56:59,220
Gosh.

1038
00:56:59,220 --> 00:57:03,940
My legs get shaky whenever I'm up here.

1039
00:57:03,940 --> 00:57:05,730
I leave everything to fate.

1040
00:57:05,730 --> 00:57:08,280
I'm extra nervous because it's the final.

1041
00:57:08,280 --> 00:57:11,310
But I won't let up and do my best until the end.

1042
00:57:11,310 --> 00:57:17,350
I'll show you how exciting a rom-com can be.

1043
00:57:17,350 --> 00:57:20,410
I think I've been very lucky so far.

1044
00:57:20,410 --> 00:57:22,300
I hope I continue to be lucky.

1045
00:57:22,300 --> 00:57:25,740
It has been an epic journey so far.

1046
00:57:25,740 --> 00:57:30,040
It's a bit sad that it's coming to an end now.

1047
00:57:30,040 --> 00:57:34,720
We'll start the final journey
toward the 100-million won prize.

1048
00:57:34,720 --> 00:57:36,940
There are people I should introduce you to.

1049
00:57:36,940 --> 00:57:41,770
I'm sure you remember the directors
who didn't make it in the death match.

1050
00:57:41,770 --> 00:57:46,750
I'll reveal the directors who are
dramatically returning for the final round.

1051
00:57:46,750 --> 00:57:48,810
Please come up to the stage.

1052
00:57:48,810 --> 00:57:51,000
Are they coming out like this? Really?

1053
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:52,620
Who are they?

1054
00:57:52,620 --> 00:57:56,250
- We are all hoping to see certain people.
- Who are they?

1055
00:57:56,250 --> 00:57:58,820
[Only two of the five directors are returning!]

1056
00:57:59,210 --> 00:58:02,690
[Who will it be?]

1057
00:58:03,910 --> 00:58:06,000
Here they come.

1058
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:10,010
[Director Han Soo Ji]

1059
00:58:10,010 --> 00:58:12,170
Welcome back.

1060
00:58:12,170 --> 00:58:14,200
[She'll prove herself once again
with "Snakes and Ladders"]

1061
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:17,350
You made a dramatic comeback. How do you feel?

1062
00:58:17,350 --> 00:58:19,910
I was so disappointed, but I'm so happy that

1063
00:58:19,910 --> 00:58:23,560
I get to show you Episodes 3, 4, and 5.

1064
00:58:23,560 --> 00:58:26,450
You were disappointed that
you didn't see the snakes last time.

1065
00:58:26,450 --> 00:58:29,010
I'll make sure you get to see them.

1066
00:58:29,010 --> 00:58:31,600
Sounds good. We have to see the snake.

1067
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:33,860
And there's one more person.

1068
00:58:33,860 --> 00:58:36,540
Who would it be? Please come up to the stage.

1069
00:58:36,540 --> 00:58:37,870
[Who's the final survivor?]

1070
00:58:37,870 --> 00:58:40,230
I can see this person's head.

1071
00:58:43,050 --> 00:58:45,560
Director Park So Rang!

1072
00:58:46,690 --> 00:58:48,510
Here she is.

1073
00:58:49,310 --> 00:58:50,630
[We missed you...]

1074
00:58:50,630 --> 00:58:52,600
Director Park So Rang.

1075
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:55,140
You didn't look so happy the last time I saw you.

1076
00:58:55,140 --> 00:58:58,010
It's nice to see you coming back
with a bright smile.

1077
00:58:58,010 --> 00:59:00,960
I was a bit hopeful to come back
through the last vote.

1078
00:59:00,960 --> 00:59:04,820
Because I didn't get that
many votes from the viewers.

1079
00:59:04,820 --> 00:59:06,340
I got 13.

1080
00:59:06,340 --> 00:59:08,770
So, I was a little bit hopeful.

1081
00:59:08,770 --> 00:59:12,800
It's a relief that I get to
show you the latter episodes.

1082
00:59:13,460 --> 00:59:18,170
Now we have the final seven directors.

1083
00:59:18,170 --> 00:59:21,650
I'll reveal the rules for the final round.

1084
00:59:21,650 --> 00:59:25,180
In the last round,
the first two episodes were revealed.

1085
00:59:25,180 --> 00:59:29,930
In the final round, you will be
judged by episodes 3, 4, and 5.

1086
00:59:29,930 --> 00:59:33,360
The Five Stars and the 50 viewers,

1087
00:59:33,360 --> 00:59:37,170
55 people in total will cast stop votes.

1088
00:59:37,170 --> 00:59:42,360
Like you always have,
if you no longer want to watch,

1089
00:59:42,360 --> 00:59:44,310
press the stop button.

1090
00:59:44,310 --> 00:59:49,480
The stop count from one episode
will roll over to the next.

1091
00:59:49,480 --> 00:59:55,580
If you get over 34 stops in total,
which is over 60% of the maximum,

1092
00:59:55,580 --> 00:59:58,600
the next episode will not play.

1093
00:59:58,600 --> 01:00:02,890
Which means you have to maintain
33 stops to play all three episodes.

1094
01:00:02,890 --> 01:00:04,360
- Huh?
- Huh?

1095
01:00:04,360 --> 01:00:05,520
You've got to be kidding me.

1096
01:00:05,520 --> 01:00:09,300
We're the final seven. They still get to stop?

1097
01:00:09,300 --> 01:00:12,850
And the stop count won't
be revealed in real time.

1098
01:00:12,850 --> 01:00:15,360
How do we determine the final winner, then?

1099
01:00:15,360 --> 01:00:18,700
We'll determine the winner based
on the average viewing time

1100
01:00:18,700 --> 01:00:22,160
among the directors who showed all episodes.

1101
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:24,420
The one with the highest record

1102
01:00:24,420 --> 01:00:27,970
will be the final winner and win 100 million won.

1103
01:00:29,940 --> 01:00:35,020
The fierce journey to make the
nation's favorite short drama.

1104
01:00:35,020 --> 01:00:38,670
Now, we are only awaiting the last moment.

1105
01:00:38,670 --> 01:00:43,300
Which series will capture the
viewers' hearts until the end?

1106
01:00:43,300 --> 01:00:51,280
Let's start the Director's Arena's
final round right now.

1107
01:00:53,070 --> 01:00:56,210
This will be fun. I can't wait.

1108
01:00:56,210 --> 01:00:58,530
We get to watch Episodes 3, 4, and 5.

1109
01:00:58,530 --> 01:01:01,760
Let's welcome the first director.

1110
01:01:01,760 --> 01:01:05,580
[Who will it be?]

1111
01:01:05,580 --> 01:01:07,460
She got 600 million views with "Eighteen,"

1112
01:01:07,460 --> 01:01:09,760
and now, she's here to win
with "Snakes and Ladders."

1113
01:01:09,760 --> 01:01:13,920
The master of detail, Director Han Soo Ji,
please come up on stage.

1114
01:01:14,820 --> 01:01:19,400
[Han Soo Ji joins the final
as an additional survivor]

1115
01:01:19,400 --> 01:01:22,340
[Serious]

1116
01:01:22,340 --> 01:01:24,380
Wow.

1117
01:01:24,380 --> 01:01:26,940
Which director are you most threatened by?

1118
01:01:26,940 --> 01:01:30,420
To be honest, it's Director Han Soo Ji.

1119
01:01:30,420 --> 01:01:34,410
There will be a snake in Episode 3.

1120
01:01:34,410 --> 01:01:39,330
She's been my first pick in every mission so far.

1121
01:01:39,330 --> 01:01:41,100
And she was my mentor, too.

1122
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:43,690
I will always consider her as my rival.

1123
01:01:43,690 --> 01:01:46,340
I think it will be Director Han Soo Ji
of "Snakes and Ladders."

1124
01:01:46,340 --> 01:01:50,600
It packed a punch from the first mission.

1125
01:01:50,600 --> 01:01:54,710
I thought the quality was worthy
of being on streaming sites.

1126
01:01:54,710 --> 01:01:58,310
I think there will be
something more in Episode 3.

1127
01:01:58,310 --> 01:02:00,260
That's why I think she'll win.

1128
01:02:00,260 --> 01:02:03,190
It's finally the final round, Director.

1129
01:02:03,190 --> 01:02:06,760
How do you feel about joining the final round?

1130
01:02:06,760 --> 01:02:09,160
I'm just very grateful.

1131
01:02:09,160 --> 01:02:15,860
I had a three-year hiatus after working nonstop.

1132
01:02:15,860 --> 01:02:18,360
I had a project that was canceled.

1133
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:23,410
While I was considering a career change...

1134
01:02:23,410 --> 01:02:31,610
Hello, I've directed many teen dramas,
including "Eighteen."

1135
01:02:31,610 --> 01:02:35,400
I'm Director Han Soo Ji. Nice to meet you.

1136
01:02:35,400 --> 01:02:37,210
Do you have any siblings?

1137
01:02:37,210 --> 01:02:39,010
My parents had two girls and two boys.

1138
01:02:39,010 --> 01:02:41,700
There are four of us.

1139
01:02:41,700 --> 01:02:44,900
One of my younger brothers is a composer.

1140
01:02:44,900 --> 01:02:48,460
He's always been my music director.

1141
01:02:48,460 --> 01:02:51,990
I'm assuming we'll work together this time, too.

1142
01:02:51,990 --> 01:02:55,220
Are there things you want to show
your parents through this show?

1143
01:02:55,220 --> 01:03:01,160
Yes, I recently told them
I signed a contract for a new project.

1144
01:03:01,160 --> 01:03:04,580
But it ended up getting canceled.
They were very upset.

1145
01:03:04,580 --> 01:03:08,390
So, I helped them at their restaurant
on New Year's Day, too.

1146
01:03:08,390 --> 01:03:13,390
They'll be so happy to see me
working on set again.

1147
01:03:14,200 --> 01:03:17,100
[The reason she never gave up on directing is...]

1148
01:03:17,100 --> 01:03:22,300
Well, I love being on set.

1149
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:29,590
I was wondering if I should
become a writer instead.

1150
01:03:29,590 --> 01:03:35,790
I want to keep going because
I enjoy working on set and editing.

1151
01:03:36,650 --> 01:03:45,260
I was grateful to tell the story
I wrote to the viewers.

1152
01:03:45,260 --> 01:03:50,770
I'm so happy that
I got to finish telling the story.

1153
01:03:50,770 --> 01:03:53,810
The thing is, Director Han Soo Ji said

1154
01:03:53,810 --> 01:03:57,700
- we'll see a lot more in Episode 3.
- That's right.

1155
01:03:57,700 --> 01:04:02,130
I'm so glad we get to see it.

1156
01:04:02,130 --> 01:04:05,300
Are you confident you'll show up
to Episode 5 without stopping?

1157
01:04:05,300 --> 01:04:08,120
I'm very nervous,

1158
01:04:08,120 --> 01:04:11,340
but I hope you enjoy them.

1159
01:04:11,340 --> 01:04:15,970
Could you tell us what happened
in Episodes 1 and 2 before we start?

1160
01:04:15,970 --> 01:04:21,520
In Episodes 1 and 2, Yun Jeong looks
for her missing sister.

1161
01:04:21,520 --> 01:04:26,210
She becomes curious about the
basement where her sister went missing,

1162
01:04:26,210 --> 01:04:29,190
and she goes over there.

1163
01:04:29,190 --> 01:04:32,280
It's what was missing in Episodes 1 and 2.

1164
01:04:32,280 --> 01:04:35,650
The story of them entering the
Snakes and Ladders game.

1165
01:04:35,650 --> 01:04:41,760
Starting in Episode 3, Yun Jeong
and Wu Min enter the game,

1166
01:04:41,760 --> 01:04:47,060
and they go through missions inside the game.

1167
01:04:47,060 --> 01:04:49,800
We'll start the judging now.

1168
01:04:49,800 --> 01:04:52,360
Play the video.

1169
01:04:52,360 --> 01:04:54,030
[Everyone is nervous]

1170
01:04:54,030 --> 01:04:55,750
- So nerve-racking.
- Fighting.

1171
01:04:55,750 --> 01:05:00,480
[Can "Snakes and Ladders" meet
everyone's expectations?]

1172
01:05:01,440 --> 01:05:04,510
I have to be back up there again?
It's driving me crazy.

1173
01:05:04,510 --> 01:05:07,860
My legs get so shaky up there.

1174
01:05:07,860 --> 01:05:12,830
[While everyone is watching]

1175
01:05:12,830 --> 01:05:15,850
[the other directors are also nervous]

1176
01:05:15,850 --> 01:05:18,150
[Will "Snakes and Ladders"
get to play up to Episode 5?]

1177
01:05:18,150 --> 01:05:20,600
["Snakes and Ladders"]

1178
01:05:20,600 --> 01:05:26,810
[Han Soo Ji's "Snakes and Ladders" Episode 3]

1179
01:05:26,810 --> 01:05:28,890
I told you not to butt in.

1180
01:05:28,890 --> 01:05:30,400
Get out of here immediately.

1181
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:33,650
What did you do here with my sister?
What did you do?

1182
01:05:33,650 --> 01:05:35,730
Can you please...

1183
01:05:38,080 --> 01:05:40,680
What's this...

1184
01:05:42,030 --> 01:05:43,720
Don't move.

1185
01:05:44,560 --> 01:05:46,200
[AI-generated footage]

1186
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:48,920
What is that...

1187
01:05:49,820 --> 01:05:51,620
Yun Jeong!

1188
01:05:57,900 --> 01:06:00,230
[Here's the snake]

1189
01:06:03,170 --> 01:06:05,510
[Getting spooked as the snake appears]

1190
01:06:05,510 --> 01:06:07,410
It's the snake.

1191
01:06:07,410 --> 01:06:09,460
[Focused]

1192
01:06:17,700 --> 01:06:19,750
Welcome.

1193
01:06:19,750 --> 01:06:23,520
You logged into the game, "Snakes and Ladders."

1194
01:06:23,520 --> 01:06:25,410
Warning. Warning. Warning.

1195
01:06:25,410 --> 01:06:28,450
Two players logged in at the same time.

1196
01:06:28,450 --> 01:06:32,120
You will be bound together
to maintain the balance of the game.

1197
01:06:32,120 --> 01:06:33,880
What's this?

1198
01:06:37,270 --> 01:06:41,960
You two formed a symbiotic relationship
where you live and die together.

1199
01:06:41,960 --> 01:06:44,700
Throw the dice.

1200
01:06:44,700 --> 01:06:46,760
Isn't this the winner?

1201
01:06:46,760 --> 01:06:49,220
[Absorbed]

1202
01:06:49,220 --> 01:06:52,070
[The stop count will not be revealed live]

1203
01:06:52,070 --> 01:06:53,800
Dice?

1204
01:06:53,800 --> 01:06:55,790
You did all this, didn't you?

1205
01:06:56,460 --> 01:06:58,390
- What do you mean?
- Explain it then.

1206
01:06:58,390 --> 01:07:02,420
Why were you there, and what was
the snake on the ceiling?

1207
01:07:06,060 --> 01:07:08,980
Tell me now. Where are we?

1208
01:07:12,050 --> 01:07:13,990
[The 10-second countdown begins]

1209
01:07:13,990 --> 01:07:15,480
What will happen? What will happen?

1210
01:07:15,480 --> 01:07:18,220
Will the next episode be played?

1211
01:07:18,220 --> 01:07:19,580
[The video stops if the
stop count is higher than 34]

1212
01:07:21,010 --> 01:07:23,200
So, this is how it works.

1213
01:07:23,200 --> 01:07:25,880
- Gosh, seriously.
- What's this?

1214
01:07:25,880 --> 01:07:28,100
Do you have to stand there for 10 seconds?

1215
01:07:28,100 --> 01:07:31,320
Will the next episode be played?

1216
01:07:31,320 --> 01:07:34,770
It plays if the stop count is fewer than 33.

1217
01:07:34,770 --> 01:07:37,410
[Will it stop now?]

1218
01:07:37,410 --> 01:07:39,580
[What will happen?]

1219
01:07:39,580 --> 01:07:41,540
[Please]

1220
01:07:42,630 --> 01:07:45,310
[Episode 4 is playing]

1221
01:07:45,710 --> 01:07:48,090
Here we go. Here we go. Here we go.

1222
01:07:48,090 --> 01:07:50,030
[What a relief]

1223
01:07:50,030 --> 01:07:52,740
If I told you, can you...

1224
01:07:52,740 --> 01:07:54,570
What? Where did she go?

1225
01:07:56,840 --> 01:07:59,390
This is like a blockbuster movie.

1226
01:08:01,300 --> 01:08:03,050
Let go.

1227
01:08:03,050 --> 01:08:05,790
Shut up and hang tight unless you want to die.

1228
01:08:13,940 --> 01:08:16,480
So impressive. How did she do it?

1229
01:08:19,340 --> 01:08:21,970
Why do you care if I die or not?

1230
01:08:21,970 --> 01:08:24,170
Didn't you hear earlier?

1231
01:08:24,170 --> 01:08:26,850
You're not the only one dying.

1232
01:08:26,850 --> 01:08:30,310
Retrieving one die due to
a player's unexpected action.

1233
01:08:30,310 --> 01:08:35,730
Now you have to reach the Box 100 with one die.

1234
01:08:35,730 --> 01:08:37,490
Give me a break.

1235
01:08:37,490 --> 01:08:40,380
I'm not interested in doing this.

1236
01:08:43,430 --> 01:08:45,410
Wake up.

1237
01:08:45,410 --> 01:08:47,450
Unless you want to end up like your sister.

1238
01:08:47,450 --> 01:08:49,800
What about my sister?

1239
01:08:49,800 --> 01:08:52,090
What happened to her?

1240
01:08:55,760 --> 01:08:58,890
- Whoa.
- Throw it if you're curious.

1241
01:09:00,350 --> 01:09:02,220
Fine.

1242
01:09:02,220 --> 01:09:05,420
Let's just do as the murderer says.

1243
01:09:11,860 --> 01:09:13,890
Box 5, Mission Snakes and Ladders.

1244
01:09:13,890 --> 01:09:16,500
- This is so fun.
- "Claustrophobia in Elevator" starts now.

1245
01:09:16,500 --> 01:09:18,870
The maximum capacity is 10 people.

1246
01:09:18,870 --> 01:09:20,490
What's this now?

1247
01:09:20,490 --> 01:09:23,190
[Episode 4 ends]

1248
01:09:23,190 --> 01:09:26,640
Why? Why does that keep popping up?

1249
01:09:26,640 --> 01:09:31,130
Episode 4 ended.
Will we be able to watch Episode 5?

1250
01:09:31,130 --> 01:09:33,080
- Wow, she did a good job.
- It's fun.

1251
01:09:33,080 --> 01:09:34,150
It's so good.

1252
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:37,770
She's been hiding all the fun elements
in Episodes 3, 4, and 5.

1253
01:09:38,550 --> 01:09:41,170
Come on, please play it.

1254
01:09:41,170 --> 01:09:43,130
[Only one episode is left...]

1255
01:09:44,730 --> 01:09:47,070
["Snakes and Ladders" Episode 5 plays]

1256
01:09:47,450 --> 01:09:49,690
[What a relief]

1257
01:09:49,690 --> 01:09:51,540
[Nerve-racking]

1258
01:09:51,540 --> 01:09:54,760
That means only ten people can get in?

1259
01:09:56,260 --> 01:09:57,920
This is getting intense.

1260
01:09:58,610 --> 01:10:00,620
Stop counting and just get in.

1261
01:10:00,620 --> 01:10:01,730
Let go!

1262
01:10:01,730 --> 01:10:03,820
You don't even know
if getting in is a good thing.

1263
01:10:03,820 --> 01:10:05,940
You need to consider the odds first.

1264
01:10:05,940 --> 01:10:08,050
Just get in!

1265
01:10:09,100 --> 01:10:10,890
The elevator reached its maximum capacity.

1266
01:10:10,890 --> 01:10:15,110
If the door doesn't close,
the cleaners will remove people.

1267
01:10:15,110 --> 01:10:17,310
- I'm scared of the cleaners.
- Cleaners?

1268
01:10:19,770 --> 01:10:22,300
- Wow.
- The snake.

1269
01:10:22,300 --> 01:10:24,490
[Love-hate relationship with the snake]

1270
01:10:27,540 --> 01:10:31,200
Watch carefully. Things will start getting messy.

1271
01:10:33,830 --> 01:10:35,530
Bastard.

1272
01:10:38,100 --> 01:10:39,330
Oh, my.

1273
01:10:40,670 --> 01:10:42,570
Why does he help me?

1274
01:10:46,210 --> 01:10:47,870
This is just a game.

1275
01:10:47,870 --> 01:10:49,370
It would've eaten us otherwise.

1276
01:10:49,370 --> 01:10:53,020
Right. If I die, he dies, too.

1277
01:10:53,020 --> 01:10:55,110
It's all because of the bracelets.

1278
01:10:55,110 --> 01:10:56,970
There will be more passengers.

1279
01:10:56,970 --> 01:10:59,510
The maximum capacity of this floor is 24.

1280
01:10:59,510 --> 01:11:00,910
What?

1281
01:11:04,410 --> 01:11:06,680
What are you doing?

1282
01:11:06,680 --> 01:11:08,430
Stay still.

1283
01:11:10,300 --> 01:11:14,060
But still, this is too close.

1284
01:11:14,060 --> 01:11:17,270
Congratulations. You skipped 19 boxes.

1285
01:11:17,270 --> 01:11:19,540
You reached Box 24.

1286
01:11:19,540 --> 01:11:20,720
[Box 24]

1287
01:11:21,770 --> 01:11:24,360
Hey, are you okay?

1288
01:11:26,030 --> 01:11:27,870
You're disgusting.

1289
01:11:29,020 --> 01:11:32,290
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

1290
01:11:32,290 --> 01:11:34,800
[Weak knees]

1291
01:11:34,800 --> 01:11:38,050
Wow, I'm so glad we got to watch this.

1292
01:11:38,050 --> 01:11:40,380
[Just as expected]

1293
01:11:40,380 --> 01:11:44,090
- The real beginning was Episode 3.
- She did a great job.

1294
01:11:44,090 --> 01:11:48,750
She went all in on Episodes 3 to 5,
thinking she'd definitely beat me.

1295
01:11:48,750 --> 01:11:50,140
[LOL]

1296
01:11:50,140 --> 01:11:53,110
Don't you think?
For Episodes 3, 4, and 5 to be so...

1297
01:11:53,110 --> 01:11:55,490
- She was too comfortable.
- Thinking she'd definitely beat me.

1298
01:11:55,490 --> 01:11:58,760
[Getting a strange feeling]

1299
01:11:58,760 --> 01:12:02,270
We saw all episodes up to Episode 5.

1300
01:12:02,270 --> 01:12:03,850
Congratulations.

1301
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:06,310
Thank you.

1302
01:12:06,310 --> 01:12:09,160
I realize it now that we saw the rest.

1303
01:12:09,160 --> 01:12:11,430
The first two episodes were just an appetizer.

1304
01:12:11,430 --> 01:12:14,050
We almost let her go without
getting to the main dish.

1305
01:12:14,050 --> 01:12:18,660
You ran at full speed in Episodes 3, 4, and 5.

1306
01:12:18,660 --> 01:12:26,260
I realized short dramas can be this spectacular.

1307
01:12:26,260 --> 01:12:32,830
[The AI technology created wild
and elaborate scenes]

1308
01:12:34,840 --> 01:12:36,260
Watch carefully.

1309
01:12:36,260 --> 01:12:38,940
It's totally different from Episodes 1 and 2.

1310
01:12:38,940 --> 01:12:42,770
You know how survival shows work.
It could've been bad.

1311
01:12:42,770 --> 01:12:45,080
It could've been such a waste.

1312
01:12:45,080 --> 01:12:48,260
- I know.
- It would've been a shame if you didn't revive.

1313
01:12:48,260 --> 01:12:49,040
Thank you.

1314
01:12:49,040 --> 01:12:52,810
I found the music noisy
in the first two episodes.

1315
01:12:52,810 --> 01:12:56,080
The sound wasn't mixed well, including the music.

1316
01:12:56,080 --> 01:12:59,980
The volume wasn't adjusted well.
It was a bit noisy.

1317
01:12:59,980 --> 01:13:02,550
The music suitable for Episodes 3 to 5
was used in the first two episodes.

1318
01:13:02,550 --> 01:13:05,100
I think that's why it bothered me.

1319
01:13:05,100 --> 01:13:07,350
It could have been a shame.

1320
01:13:07,350 --> 01:13:10,450
Anyway, time went by quickly. I enjoyed them.

1321
01:13:10,450 --> 01:13:11,960
Thank you.

1322
01:13:11,960 --> 01:13:16,420
I found it very speedy and jam-packed.

1323
01:13:16,420 --> 01:13:20,740
I was overwhelmed watching it.
I couldn't breathe.

1324
01:13:20,740 --> 01:13:22,550
I held my breath watching it.

1325
01:13:22,550 --> 01:13:26,280
We watched up to Episode 5,
but I want to watch the rest.

1326
01:13:26,280 --> 01:13:30,080
- Thank you.
- I'm curious what would happen next.

1327
01:13:30,080 --> 01:13:32,930
We just heard about this,

1328
01:13:32,930 --> 01:13:38,120
but I heard your grandfather
passed away while filming.

1329
01:13:38,120 --> 01:13:41,730
To hear such news...

1330
01:13:41,730 --> 01:13:45,590
It must've been very difficult
for you while filming.

1331
01:13:45,590 --> 01:13:48,420
You must've gone through so much.

1332
01:13:50,480 --> 01:13:55,870
I still had to finish everything
before the deadline.

1333
01:13:56,590 --> 01:14:00,480
I didn't get to be there the entire time.

1334
01:14:02,160 --> 01:14:06,720
Thank you so much for finishing your work.

1335
01:14:06,720 --> 01:14:10,890
Thankfully, we got to watch up to Episode 5.

1336
01:14:10,890 --> 01:14:14,220
I think that alone is such a relief.

1337
01:14:14,220 --> 01:14:16,700
You've been through so much. Thank you.

1338
01:14:16,700 --> 01:14:18,890
[Could she be the one to win 100 million?]

1339
01:14:18,890 --> 01:14:23,390
You can go back to your seat
and wait for the results.

1340
01:14:23,390 --> 01:14:25,590
The 100-million won prize.

1341
01:14:25,590 --> 01:14:28,570
The last battle to determine one winner.

1342
01:14:28,570 --> 01:14:30,910
The grand final round has begun.

1343
01:14:30,910 --> 01:14:32,280
My goal is to win, of course.

1344
01:14:32,280 --> 01:14:34,100
It would be nice if I won.

1345
01:14:34,100 --> 01:14:35,600
I don't want to lose.

1346
01:14:35,600 --> 01:14:37,680
I'll beat them all and win 100 million won.

1347
01:14:37,680 --> 01:14:38,970
What?

1348
01:14:38,970 --> 01:14:41,610
Why would you run away from your wedding?

1349
01:14:42,550 --> 01:14:44,430
I'm glad I ran into you today.

1350
01:14:44,430 --> 01:14:46,470
The familiar feeling can be powerful.

1351
01:14:46,470 --> 01:14:49,550
The first two episodes were just an appetizer.

1352
01:14:52,850 --> 01:14:54,800
[However]

1353
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:58,040
Will the next episode play?

1354
01:14:58,040 --> 01:14:59,950
This really is no joke.

1355
01:14:59,950 --> 01:15:01,470
I got bored and tired.

1356
01:15:01,470 --> 01:15:03,500
I don't think I need to watch the next episode.

1357
01:15:03,500 --> 01:15:04,460
Something went wrong.

1358
01:15:04,460 --> 01:15:05,650
It was a hellish moment.

1359
01:15:05,650 --> 01:15:07,200
It was so shocking to me.

1360
01:15:07,200 --> 01:15:11,710
Which series will capture the
viewers' hearts until the end?

1361
01:15:11,710 --> 01:15:14,720
The final winner is...
